categories.title: Recent GitHub Issues in elizaOS/eliza Repository

content.text:
Several issues have been recently reported in the elizaOS/eliza GitHub repository:

1. Installation Issues: User 'small-talk' reported in issue #3882 that they are unable to progress beyond the 'pnpm install and build' stage.

2. Tweet Processing Error: User 'fction' reported in issue #3877 an error when processing an undefined tweet.

3. Social AI Agent Building Guide: User '552020' created issue #3880 regarding fixing a guide titled 'Building a Social AI Agent in 15 Minutes'.

4. JSON Null Values: User 'aiden-cao' reported issue #3886 concerning the conversion of JSON null values.

5. Chinese Community Group: User 'aiqubits' created issue #3885 about a Chinese AI Agent community discussion group (中文AI Agent 社区交流群).

categories.title: Recent Pull Requests in elizaOS/eliza Repository

content.text:
Several pull requests have been submitted to the elizaOS/eliza repository addressing various fixes:

1. PR #3881 by think-in-universe fixes NEAR AI image generation functionality.

2. PR #3876 by ChristopherTrimboli addresses missing moment rollup external and the-org issues.

3. PR #3878 by AIFlowML fixes issues with the plugin-telegram component.

4. PR #3883 by wtfsayo resolves problems with chat bubbles in the interface.

These pull requests represent ongoing maintenance and bug fixing efforts in the eliza project.

Over the past two days (March 9-11, 2025), the elizaos/eliza repository showed consistent development activity. There were a total of 3 new pull requests with 2 successfully merged. The repository also received 5 new issues during this period. Contributor engagement remained strong with 10 active contributors on March 9-10, decreasing to 5 active contributors on March 10-11.
